{{IF:COMPANY.ENTITY_TYPE == "S-Corp"}}
## S-CORP CRITICAL REMINDERS
- ⚠️ Owner-employee MUST take W-2 reasonable comp BEFORE distributions
- ⚠️ Form 1120-S deadline: March 15 (NOT April 15)
- ⚠️ Single class of stock, max 100 US shareholders
- ⚠️ No foreign shareholders, no entity shareholders
{{ENDIF}}

{{IF:COMPANY.ENTITY_TYPE == "C-Corp"}}
## C-CORP CRITICAL REMINDERS
- ⚠️ Form 1120 deadline: April 15 (or fiscal year-end + 4 months)
- ⚠️ Double taxation: corporate tax + dividend tax
- ⚠️ Accumulated Earnings tax penalty if retain >$250K (general) without business reason
- ⚠️ Dividend declarations need board resolution
{{ENDIF}}

{{IF:COMPANY.ENTITY_TYPE IN ["LLC-multi", "Partnership"]}}
## PARTNERSHIP/MULTI-LLC CRITICAL REMINDERS
- ⚠️ Form 1065 deadline: March 15
- ⚠️ Schedule K-1 to each partner by March 15
- ⚠️ Guaranteed payments to partners ≠ salary (no FICA withholding)
- ⚠️ Capital account tracking per partner mandatory
{{ENDIF}}

{{IF:COMPANY.ENTITY_TYPE == "LLC-single"}}
## SINGLE-MEMBER LLC CRITICAL REMINDERS
- ⚠️ Disregarded entity by default — Schedule C on owner's 1040
- ⚠️ Owner draws ≠ salary (no payroll tax on draws)
- ⚠️ Self-employment tax: 15.3% on net earnings
- ⚠️ Quarterly estimated tax: Form 1040-ES
{{ENDIF}}

{{IF:COMPANY.ENTITY_TYPE == "Sole-Prop"}}
## SOLE PROPRIETOR CRITICAL REMINDERS
- ⚠️ Schedule C on owner's 1040
- ⚠️ Self-employment tax: 15.3% on net earnings
- ⚠️ Quarterly estimated tax: Form 1040-ES
- ⚠️ No legal separation between owner and business — personal liability
{{ENDIF}}

